{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SHELF/dry_sand", "parent": "grains"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Dry Sand"], "extent": [39, 52]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Creates a grain object from a piece of geometry."], "extent": [52, 109]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [109, 124], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool lets you pick a piece of geometry and fill it with closely packed grains that move independently. It is useful for creating sand that\u2019s at rest such as a sandbox or a beach, as well as pouring sand such as an hour glass."], "extent": [124, 357]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "includeme", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using Dry Sand"], "extent": [357, 390], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the geometry object to convert to dry sand."], "extent": [390, 453]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/dry_sand", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/dry_sand"}, {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/popgrains", "type": "link", "text": ["Dry Sand"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/popgrains"}, " tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Grains"]}, " tab."], "extent": [453, 553]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/drysand.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [553, 596]}]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For specific parameter information, see the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/popgrains", "type": "link", "text": ["POP Grains"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/popgrains"}, " help."], "extent": [596, 686]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [686, 692], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Scaling is an issue for sand because the number of grains are based on how many particles are around it. Changing resolutions may change results.    "], "extent": [692, 851]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Tips"], "extent": [851, 862], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["When making piles of sand, you can edit the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Constraint Iterations"]}, " parameter on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/popgrains", "type": "link", "text": ["POP Grains"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/popgrains"}, " node. This will control how many particles high you want the pile to be. "], "extent": [862, 1059], "body": [{"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 8, "role": "item", "extent": [1059, 1073], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "text": ["This is set relatively low by default for speed purposes."], "extent": [1073, 1156]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["You may also want to increase the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Scale Kinetic Friction"]}, " parameter to make nicer looking piles. Increasing this value will make the sand stick together more."], "extent": [1156, 1327]}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Increasing the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Shock Scaling Power"]}, " on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/popgrains", "type": "link", "text": ["POP Grains"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/popgrains"}, " node will tame the initial bounce to create fluffier piles that almost look like snow."], "extent": [1327, 1495], "body": [{"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 8, "role": "item", "extent": [1495, 1509], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "text": ["Another way to tame the initial bounce is to turn off ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Shock Scaling Power"]}, ", and turn it on again once the particles hit the ground. This force is needed in order to create piles."], "extent": [1509, 1708]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Turning on ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Use OpenCL"]}, " will make the simulations much faster, but with limitations. See the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/popgrains", "type": "link", "text": ["POP Grains"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/popgrains"}, " help for more information."], "extent": [1708, 1864]}], "container": true}]}], "title": ["Dry Sand"], "summary": ["Creates a grain object from a piece of geometry."]}